wanting to open the door and jump into the battle that no doubt waited
for him on the other side of the door, and yet something else screamed
caution at him. Why would someone rush headlong into an enemy base,
knowing that they would quickly bring to bear all the security measures
that had on the intruder.

Pressing button on the control panel beside the room door he checked
the condition of the room. The result was of course a single occupant,
and that the room was totally shielded and powered down. So the room
that could be an arena for battle was now doubling for a temporary
cell. 

&quot;Perceptor&quot; Myrmidon called over the short range intrabase
communications, &quot;Report to my location, I believe I have our intruder
pinned.&quot;

